Class AbstractBinaryFunction<L,R,O>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBinaryPredicate, BinaryFunctionChain, BinaryFunctionGroup, Cast, DualFunctionChain, ExceptionMappingBinaryFunction, ExtractString, GetElement, InvokeMethod, Print, SetElement

    public abstract class AbstractBinaryFunction<L,R,O>
extends AbstractFunction<L,O>
implements BinaryFunction<L,R,O>
    An abstract base implementation of the BinaryFunction interface. It accepts the initial right value for unary function evaluations as a constructor argument.

      • paramsEqual

        protected boolean paramsEqual(AbstractFunction<?,?> rOther)
        This method must be overridden by subclasses that define additional function parameters to compare these parameters for equality with another function instance. It will be invoked by this classes' implementation of AbstractFunction.equals(Object) after the standard equality checks have been performed. A subclass can safely assume that the other function argument is not NULL and of exactly the same class as itself. The default implementation always returns TRUE.
        Overrides:
        paramsEqual in class AbstractFunction<L,O>
        Parameters:
        rOther - The other function to compare the parameters with
        Returns:
        TRUE if all parameters are equal to that of the other function

        This method must be overridden by subclasses that define additional function parameters to calculate a hash code for these parameters.
